Material Information Summary

Type: Exploration Results Update

  • New Target Area Identified:
  • MT and seismic surveys reveal a large (~7km²) conductive zone ~3km northeast of previous drilling (VUD 008).
  • VUD 008 intersected 179.75m mineralized basement with grades of 0.19% Cu, 0.10g/t Au, 68g/t Mo, including a higher-grade zone of 0.63% Cu, 0.28g/t Au, 107g/t Mo.

  • Conductive zone extends ~4km northeast, open at depth (>5km), with potential for IOCG-style mineralization.

  • Geophysical Insights:

  • Low-resistivity anomaly (<30 Ω.m) suggests possible fluid pathways for mineralization.

  • Alignment with known basement faults increases prospectivity.

  • Next Steps:

  • Further exploration planned (details pending).

No capital/financial data or timetable disclosed.

Material Information Summary: ASX Prospectus - Amplia Therapeutics Limited (ASX: ATX)

Capital Raising Overview

Статус: Share Purchase Plan (SPP)
- Structure: SPP + SPP Shortfall Offer (for institutional investors if undersubscribed).
- Target Raise: A$2.5M (with ability to accept oversubscriptions up to A$10M total).
- SPP Price: Lower of:
- Fixed price of A$0.23/share (Placement Offer Price), or
- 5% discount to 5-day VWAP before Closing Date.
- Key Dates:
- Record Date: 22 July 2025.
- Closing Date: 22 August 2025.
- Results Announcement: 26 August 2025.
- AGM (Approval): 27 August 2025.
- Trading of New Shares: Expected 1 September 2025.

Use of Proceeds

Total raised funds (up to A$27.5M before costs) will be allocated to:
- Clinical Trials:
- ACCENT (Phase 2a pancreatic cancer trial completion).
- AMPLICITY (dose escalation/comparison).
- Initiation of kRAS and ovarian cancer trials.
- Manufacturing (CMC): A$6M.
- Working capital & costs.

Capital Structure Impact

  • Current Shares Outstanding: 486.5M.
  • New Shares Issued: Up to 43.5M (if SPP reaches A$10M at A$0.23/share).
  • Market Cap (at A$0.23): A$117M–125M (depending on raise size).

Key Risks

  • Clinical Trials: No guarantee of success; topline data for ACCENT due August 2025.
  • Funding: Future capital needs may dilute shareholders.
  • Regulatory: Approval risks for trials/commercialization.
  • R&D Tax Rebate: Reliance on government incentives (~A$8.2M expected).

Additional Material Details

  • Lead Manager: Bell Potter Securities (not underwritten but backstopped for A$2.5M shortfall).
  • Eligibility: Shareholders in AU/NZ as of 22 July 2025; max A$100k per holder.
  • Dilution: Non-participating shareholders face dilution (up to ~9% at full raise).

Action Required

Eligible shareholders must apply via BPAY/EFT by 22 August 2025.

No material omissions or discrepancies identified.

Material Information Summary: Forrestania Resources Acquires British Hill Gold Project

Key Transaction Details

  • Acquisition: Binding agreement to acquire 100% of IMD Gold (owner of British Hill Gold Project).
  • Consideration:
  • Upfront: 34,772,727 FRS shares (valued at A$3.825M based on 20-day VWAP of A$0.11).
  • Deferred: Potential additional shares or cash (up to A$6M total consideration) if 20-day VWAP <A$0.174 within 3 months.
  • Conditions: Due diligence, ASX approvals, and third-party consents. Expected completion by 19 August 2025.

Project Highlights

  • Resource: 1.17Mt at 1.5g/t Au (55,888 oz Au) – JORC compliant, predominantly open-pitable.
  • Breakdown:
    • Indicated: 717kt @ 1.33g/t (30,718 oz)
    • Inferred: 308kt @ 2.41g/t (23,907 oz).
  • Metallurgy: 83–91% recoveries via conventional CIL processing.
  • Location: WA mining lease (M77/1256) with adjacent exploration licenses.

Capital Structure Impact

  • Shares Issued: 34.8M new shares (within Listing Rule 7.1 capacity; no shareholder approval required).

Next Steps

  • Timeline: Due diligence within 21 days; completion by 19 August 2025.

Omitted: JORC technical details, drilling tables, and non-material operational commentary.
